    I-perm-004 (#1198) slice 1: span_resolver keystone — boilerplate classifier + entailing-span argmax
    
    PURE, INERT (not yet wired -> zero production behavior change). The verifier drops a large share of
    real claims because the [#ev] token points at a non-entailing span even though a genuinely-entailing
    span sits ELSEWHERE in the same row (drb_76 verification_details, confirmed on saved data: 40
    verified / 41 dropped of 81; 29 `entailment_failed` with in-row support). The existing recovery
    (`_try_reanchor`, #1189) accepts the FIRST passing candidate with no boilerplate filter and no
    best-span ranking -> drb_76 re-anchored to the row TITLE. This keystone replaces first-passing with
    a BOILERPLATE-AWARE ARGMAX (RARR re-point; ALCE precision; MiniCheck max-over-evidence).
    
    `span_resolver.py` (pure, no network/LLM):
    - `classify_span(text) -> {prose|title|header|affiliation|nav_link|url|altmetric|reference_list}`:
      deterministic boilerplate classifier (specific patterns first; title-case ratio separates an
      8-word title from an 8-word prose sentence; nav detected by keyword OR pipe/bullet link-bar).
    - `resolve_best_entailing_span(direct_quote, sentence, candidate_spans, *, judge_fn, numeric_match_fn,
      top_k)`: cheap lexical PRE-rank (prose-first) -> judge ONLY top_k -> ARGMAX over entailing
      candidates, preferring prose over boilerplate then confidence. Returns the Decision-B per-claim
      fields (best_span, provenance_quality, confidence, entailed) or None when nothing in-row entails.
    
    SAFETY (the §-1.1-lethal risk is MANUFACTURING support): the resolver NEVER decides entailment — the
    INJECTED `judge_fn` (the binding gate, run allow_local_window_fallback=False at the wiring site) does;
    the resolver only CHOOSES among candidates the judge accepted. Boilerplate is a deprioritization +
    confidence PENALTY, never a fabrication path (a title-only-supported claim is returned LABELED
    low-confidence, never silently verified). Confidence is entailment-dominated, not lexical.
    
    Codex slice-1 diff gate: APPROVE iter1 (zero P0/P1); the two classifier P2s (pipe-separated nav
    link-bar + journal-chrome keyword list mis-reading as prose@conf-1.0) are fixed here — strictly
    additive boilerplate detection (prose->nav_link only lowers confidence, never an over-credit).
    
    Tests (9 green): classifier buckets incl. nav link-bar/chrome; argmax picks entailing prose over a
    lexically-similar title; title-only support is labeled low (never silent high); None when nothing
    entails; only a judge-accepted span is ever returned; judge calls bounded by top_k; numeric mismatch
    lowers confidence.
    
    Next slices: wire into provenance_generator (replace gap-#18 accept block to RE-POINT + replace
    _try_reanchor first-passing with this argmax) and strict_verify; #1180 widening prompt + labeled bakeoff.
    
